<meta name="socialpost1" content="This is the story of how one of the most influential climate papers in history came to exist thanks to one of the companies most responsible for causing the climate crisis — and one with a financial stake in the technologies described in the paper." />
<meta name="socialpost2" content="BP execs were deeply involved in shaping a highly influential climate science paper. The authors not only discussed ideas with the oil company but, in a departure from academic norms, passed drafts back and forth and welcomed extensive feedback." />
<meta name="socialpost3" content="For decades, people learning how to mitigate global warming learned from the landmark paper “Wedges.” What they didn’t learn: “Wedges” was significantly shaped by BP — one of the single global entities most responsible for causing climate change." />
<meta name="socialpost4" content="BP not only funded the research behind the influential “Wedges” climate science paper, but company execs even tried to revise versions of it. “Chaps, I have had a go at rewriting the paper,” a BP climate adviser wrote the researchers at one point." />
<meta name="socialpost5" content="Scientists and ethics observers now say an influential climate paper known as “Wedges” may not have been seen as credible or earned its acclaim had the extent of BP’s involvement — which went far beyond funding the research — been fully disclosed." />
